Two other points relating to scope of the cleaning and blowing works were debated during trial.  They now appear relatively insignificant and can be dealt with shortly.  First, there was a dispute about whether thermocouples in the reactor bay piping should be removed before the systems were blown.  SABIC insisted that they should be and SCL ultimately agreed in mid-October 2008

 {F/980/2588} 
	      .  Nothing turns on this dispute.  Second, there was a dispute about whether SCL refused to clean storage tanks.  On this issue I accept the evidence of Mr Buckley that an additional chemical cleaning rig was brought to site to carry out cleaning including the tanks in question.  Again, nothing turns on this.

