First, they submit that a number of faults may have occurred due to a change to the DCS after SCL had carried out its loop test.  While it is not possible to exclude the possibility that this may have happened, a modification to the DCS would have been carried out under the Change Control  procedure and so should not have been registered as a fault

 SABIC has not disclosed a log of DCS modifications; but I accept SCL’s submission that there would have been one. 
